The body of a 30-year-old man was found next to the road by residents, who reported it to police. Kraaifontein community policing forum spokesperson Sila Mawethu said he returned from the Eastern Cape yesterday and had not received 
much information on the 
incident. He said news that the person was a jogger and may have been targeted by robbers was unconfirmed. The victim's identity was not yet known. Police spokesperson FC van Wyk said police had opened a murder investigation following the discovery. “The death of an unknown male in his thirties is being investigated after his body was discovered on the Lichtenburg Road in Fisantekraal yesterday (Sunday) morning. "The circumstances are being investigated and no one has been arrested as yet,” said Van Wyk. Anyone with information is urged to contact Kraaifontein police on 021 980 5500 or Crime Stop on 086 001 0111.